questionRound.0.question.9.answer: I assumed everyone was picking the box they thought would get them the most units.

I looked to see if there was anyone who had a clear choice regardless of the actions of others. If this did not occur  as I soon observed it did not  I looked at what the last player would choose and how it would work out if I went first. I would see what would give me the most benefit possible  considering what else would later occur. It was a train to see if I would end up in my starting box. So I started with the highest number and worked out all the moves  then I went on to try the second highest number and worked on everyone's moves  etc. If I was second  I would use that data to see what everyone else would benefit the most from and then I found what would benefit me most after those selections occured. If I was second to last  I looked to see who would influence how much I make and who influences them. I would figure out their decision and work to my decision. If I was last  I just chose the best option for myself.

I decided that if I was one of the first three players to choose  I should go for the option that did NOT contain the highest payoff possible.   However  if I was the last to choose  I would go for the option that would give me the best payoff based on what other people had already picked.  Other than that  unfortunately  my strategy was not very precise.

I developed the strategy to see what the last person in the sequence would choose  based off of the most possible points they could attain. From that result I then backtracked to see what each person in reverse order would choose (Given that each person would choose the greatest possible amount). |  | If I was the first in order  I would do this method  but twice  considering whether I would choose X or Y. Then  based off of those results  I would then choose the one that would reward me with the greatest possible result.

It was easy. You run through the possibilities and then select the chice that would give you the most in the end  assuming everyone else knows what they're doing. Usually that meant selecting the choice that gave you the second highest number possible for you to get.  |  | It was only annoying when people made silly mistakes that affected them AND you  but gave one other person the highest.

Every time when I  get to choose first  I will pick the one has less variance in number(28 & 6  vs. 4& 32) in the hope that I will get 28.  |  | Every time when I was able to see other people's choice  I will base my choice on theirs and assuming everyone is choosing the one that's  most beneficial to them.
IF ORANGE  ALWAYS PICKED HIGHEST NUMBER. | IF FIRST POCKED ROW WITH HIGHER VALUES TO INCREASE CHANCES OF GETTING MORE TOKENS | IF 2ND OR 3RD  TYPICALLY PICKED 2ND HIGHEST VALUE
Choose the one that benefits me the most  and predict what others will choose since everyone will choose the one that is most advantageous to them.

I tended to work backwards to figure out what each person would choose. If I was first  then I would contemplate choosing X and then work backwards to find out what the last person would choose  then the third person  then the second  and then finally find out what I would get. If it was the smaller value  then I would repeat this process contemplating choosing Y instead. This almost always worked out to give me one of the two higher values that I could earn.
Figuring out whatever the last person will choose  then the second last person  etc.

If I went first I always picked the row that would give me the best chance at winning. If I went last I obviously looked at what the first role picked in order to maximize my profits. If I went second or third I would look to see what roles ahead would most likely pick (based on maximizing their profits) and then judging on what I thought they would pick I would see which row that corresponded to on my payoff chart and then picked the best corresponding cell in that row. I also sometimes had the tendency to look at who's payoff I was affecting and try to minimize their profits.

if you are the first one to choose  go for the column that has the second large number; | if you are not the first one to choose  look at what the first one chooses  then use that to guess what others would choose in an inverse sequence. That way  you can find out which one is better to select for yourself.
